getValue

public final Object getValue()
Returns the value of a Name reference in a MVEL program whose name is given by the return value of this NameResolver's getName() method.

If a suitable value cannot be determined, then the empty string ("") is returned.

This method never returns null.

Specified by:

setValue

public final void setValue(Object value)
Experimental; puts a Name into the Named that is affiliated with this NameResolver, provided that it is an instance of AbstractNamed.

In general, if the conditions described in the parameters section below are not met, this method does nothing.

Specified by:
setValue in interface VariableResolver
Parameters:
value - the value for a new name; may be null, a NameValue, a String or a Name. If it is null, then any Name indexed under this NameResolver's affiliated NameType present in the affiliated AbstractNamed will be removed. If it is either a NameValue, a String or a Name, then it is converted common-sensically into a NameValue and is installed into the AbstractNamed in such a way that a subsequent call to getValue() will return the expected result.
